    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-03-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-03-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="828"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d828">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hardy</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-03-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 8, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 205.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my No. 188, of February 5 last,
                    reporting the case of Jorge Grau y Ortegueira, and asking whether, under the
                    circumstances stated, he was entitled to protection as a citizen of Porto Rico,
                    I have the honor to inform you that the certificate of nationality issued to him
                    by the consul at Cadiz having been disregarded by the Spanish authorities at
                    that place and the said Jorge Grau having been cited to appear for military
                    duty, I was obliged to act without waiting for the Department’s views. My
                    protest to the under secretary of state was promptly accepted, telegraphic
                    orders to annul the citation and respect the consul’s certificate were at once
                    issued, and the incident satisfactorily closed.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Arthur S. Hardy.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
